overview.eaover:
A comprehensive list of metric creation steps is included in the Processing Steps.
			The grain data used are for grain only, not silage. When possible, 2007 census data was used. When 2007 census data was not available, 2007 survey data was used instead. County data was used first, then state data when county data was unavailable, then national data when state data was unavailable. 
			CDL values were categorized as follows: 
			Corn: 1, 225, 226, 237, 241. 
			Barley: 21, 235, 237, 254, 233. 
			Cotton: 2, 232, 238, 239. 
			Durum wheat: 22, 230, 234. 
			Oats: 28, 226, 240. 
			Rye: 27. 
			Rice: 3. 
			Sorghum: 4, 234 235, 236. 
			Spring Wheat: 23. 
			Soybeans: 5, 26, 239, 240, 241, 254. 
			Winter Wheat: 24, 26, 225, 236, 238. 
			Double crops were counted once for each crop. 
			The following conversion factors were used to convert crop yields to tons: 
			1 bu wheat: 0.03, 
			1 bu soybeans: 0.03, 
			1 bu corn (shelled): 0.028, 
			1 bu sorghum: 0.028, 
			1 bu barley: 0.024, 
			1 bu oats: 0.016, 
			1 bu rye: 0.028, 	
			1 bale cotton: 0.24, 
			1 cwt rice: 0.05. 
			-----------------
